item.description: Testing Methodology Although the testing of a cooler appears to be a simple task, there are many factors that need to be considered. Proper thermal testing cannot be performed with a cooler mounted on a single chip, for multiple reasons. Some of these reasons include the instability of the thermal load and the inability to fully control and/or monitor it, as well as the inaccuracy of the chip-integrated sensors.
